snippet.textDisplay: One thing is for certain, she will have to throw better than a 91.12 three dart average to go much further. A big thing has been made about Billie Jean King sending her support about being equal to the men but the PDC are talking about a women`s tournament similar to the BDO one but surely, equality would mean actually playing the men and winning and there is no reason why the cant but I feel that it will be just the same a tennis. The Wimbledon women's champion gets the same prize money as the men but they only play three sets, not the five that the men have to play and the fact is that most of the men that lose in the first rround would beat the women`s champion and get just a fraction of the money that the women`s champion gets. So, basically, the women are rewarded more than the players that would beat them. This will be even worse in darts because there is no reason why a woman cannot beat a man at a sport that does not rely on size or strength. If women like Fallon Sherrock want equality, they should play the men and ignore any women`s tournaments but of course they wont because they know that ant the moment, the men player will set a much higher average, unless they have the crowd trying to put them off by booing every throw.

snippet.textDisplay: I think the walk on song "Trouble' by Pink would suite Fallon. Just like in her first game, she payed perfect matchplay darts: high scores when she needed it and finishing to hurt her opponent. It is clear that Mensur lost the game before he went on stage. In the first set he had 3 darts to finish. The crowd were not really booing at that moment, but he missed them. Him smiling going of stage after the first set said it all. I have been to PL matches which were much more noisy and certainly the crowd were booing, but what did you think Taylor had to go through in Scotland and vice versa Gary in the beginning in the UK. Them both always produces the goods. Well Hollywood wants to be in a show, now he will be. If he plays like in the PL, Fallon won't have a chance, but when he doesn't she will have one if she combines the scoring of the first game and the finishing of the second game. The one thing I enjoyed the most with her and Nico Kurz is their composure. Both young people using the occasion to give a great performance. For the future of women darts it would be great if they can combine their own tour with the challenger tour or the youth tour. I agree with Fallon that the women need to be challenged more but in a way that they will not be killed. May I remind that it was only when MVG starting playing matches on the then challenger tour again that he regained his confidence after about 3 years of torment with the seniors; I have seen some bloke called Peter M☺ laughing in his face. MVG repaid with interest by the way. Good luck to Chris & Fallon, may the best dartsplayer win on the night!
